    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-04T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="3"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d3">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3387: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-04T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 4, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 4—4 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. Following from American Consul General at Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“January 3, noon. Headquarters has announced that
                                <persName>Chinhsien</persName> was occupied at 4:40 this morning by
                            Muro brigade.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
